  "name": "Policy engine | Gemini CLI",
  "description": "The Gemini CLI includes a powerful policy engine that provides fine-grained\ncontrol over tool execution. It allows users and administrators to define rules\nthat determine whether a tool call should be...",
  "step": [
    {
      "@type": "HowToStep",
      "position": 1,
      "text": "Create the policy directoryif it doesn\u2019t exist:Terminal windowmkdir-p~/.gemini/policies"
    },
    {
      "@type": "HowToStep",
      "position": 2,
      "text": "Create a new policy file(e.g.,~/.gemini/policies/my-rules.toml). You\ncan use any filename ending in.toml; all such files in this directory\nwill be loaded and combined:[[rule]]toolName =\"run_shell_command\"commandPrefix =\"git status\"decision =\"allow\"priority =100"
    },
    {
      "@type": "HowToStep",
      "position": 3,
      "text": "Run a commandthat triggers the policy (e.g., ask Gemini CLI togit status). The tool will now execute automatically without prompting for\nconfirmation."
    }
  ],
